stylometry: The trade off between price and demand is that as price rises demand typically falls. Therefore if a manager raises the price on a popular product or service he/she runs the risk of the demand dropping. Depending on how much demand drops this may cause a loss in revenue. Likewise, if an unpopular product or service has a drop in price the demand may rise. Again, depending on how much the price is dropped and how much demand has risen there may be a loss in revenue. If I was solving this in a model I would find out what my desired revenue per product or service was. I would also have to know the approximate affect on demand I would have with each increment of price drop. For example, if I lower the price $1 how much does demand go up. I could then create a graph and find were the line correlated with my desired revenue. There is also the possibility that it would not correlate with my desired revenue.
